<h2 class="sectionedit1" id="dnkk_kano_transition_table">DNKK Kano Transition Table</h2>
<div class="level2">

</div>
<!-- EDIT{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;plugin_include_start&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ssa-transition-table&quot;,&quot;hid&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;secid&quot;:2,&quot;range&quot;:&quot;0-&quot;} --><div class="plugin_include_content plugin_include__ssa-transition-table">
<div class="level2">
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Some airfields within SSA have published fixed Transition Levels. In this case, use the published transition level. </div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> CAUTION – With a fixed Transition Level, it may mean less than 1,000 ft separation exists between aircraft operating at the Transition Altitude and Transition Level depending on the QNH.</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Where a fixed transition level is not published, use the table below to determine the transition level.</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="table sectionedit4"><table class="inline">
	<thead>
	<tr class="row0">
		<th class="col0 leftalign"> QNH           </th><th class="col1 leftalign"> 2000  </th><th class="col2 leftalign"> 3000  </th><th class="col3 leftalign"> 4000  </th><th class="col4 leftalign"> 5000  </th><th class="col5 leftalign"> 6000  </th><th class="col6 leftalign"> 7000  </th><th class="col7 leftalign"> 8000  </th><th class="col8 leftalign"> 9000  </th><th class="col9"> 10000 </th><th class="col10"> 14000 </th>
	</tr>
	</thead>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> 1060 - 1050   </td><td class="col1"> FL020 </td><td class="col2"> FL030 </td><td class="col3"> FL040 </td><td class="col4"> FL050 </td><td class="col5"> FL060 </td><td class="col6"> FL070 </td><td class="col7"> FL080 </td><td class="col8"> FL090 </td><td class="col9"> FL100 </td><td class="col10"> FL140 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> 1049 - 1032   </td><td class="col1"> FL025 </td><td class="col2"> FL035 </td><td class="col3"> FL045 </td><td class="col4"> FL055 </td><td class="col5"> FL065 </td><td class="col6"> FL075 </td><td class="col7"> FL085 </td><td class="col8"> FL095 </td><td class="col9"> FL105 </td><td class="col10"> FL145 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row3">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> 1031 - 1014   </td><td class="col1"> FL030 </td><td class="col2"> FL040 </td><td class="col3"> FL050 </td><td class="col4"> FL060 </td><td class="col5"> FL070 </td><td class="col6"> FL080 </td><td class="col7"> FL090 </td><td class="col8"> FL100 </td><td class="col9"> FL110 </td><td class="col10"> FL150 </td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row4">
		<td class="col0 leftalign"> 1013 - 995    </td><td class="col1"> FL035 </td><td class="col2"> FL045 </td><td class="col3"> FL055 </td><td class="col4"> FL065 </td><td class="col5"> FL075 </td><td class="col6"> FL085 </td><td class="col7"> FL095 </td><td class="col8"> FL105 </td><td class="col9"> FL115 </td><td class="col10"> FL155 </td>
	</tr>
</table></div>
<!-- EDIT{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;table&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;hid&quot;:&quot;table&quot;,&quot;secid&quot;:4,&quot;range&quot;:&quot;484-977&quot;} --><ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Although the Transition Level may not be a ‘whole’ flight level. Commonly the ‘Lowest Useful Flight Level’ will be the nearest ‘whole’ flight level. E.g. FL85 would be FL90 (Always round up)</div>
</li>
</ul>

</div>
<!-- EDIT{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;plugin_include_editbtn&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Dynamic Transition&quot;,&quot;hid&quot;:null,&quot;secid&quot;:5,&quot;range&quot;:&quot;0-&quot;} --><!-- EDIT{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;plugin_include_end&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;ssa-transition-table&quot;,&quot;hid&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;secid&quot;:3,&quot;range&quot;:&quot;0-&quot;} --></div>
<div class="level2">

